        "timestamp": "2019-12-10 09:28:32.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Patch Set 1:\n> \n> What is PV and PVC?\n\nPV is Persistent Volume. When we deploy ONAP, as we are using an NFS share, we must create a folder in this folder for the datas we need to keep. When we'll move to dynamic PV, it will be created automatically by the storage class \nPVC is Persistent Volume Claim. This is the way to bind a \"PV\" into deployment or statefulset.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
